description: A user of the site pointed out that ٩ is the number 9 in Arabic and ۶ is a character called a humza from the Urdu and Arabic alphabets. It’s exciting to learn about other alphabets, and these emojis all use these two characters for their arms. It looks like their arms are thrown up in joy.
